But `CheckpointTranscriptStart` matters if there are multiple deferred checkpoint IDs. And `BaseCommit` matters for shadow branch resolution of subsequent deferred checkpoints.\\n\\nIn the Cursor case (single commit per turn), this isn't a problem. But for correctness, the deferred condensation in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` should update the state similarly.\\n\\nLet me now formalize the complete plan.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation Plan\\n\\n### Approach: Record checkpoint ID on condensation attempt + deferred CondenseSession at stop time\\n\\nThis is Approach B with refinements. It ensures the checkpoint is created with full, correct metadata (attribution, files touched, summary, token usage) when the transcript becomes available.\\n\\n### Step-by-step changes\\n\\n#### 1. Add `condenseAttempted` field to `postCommitActionHandler` (manual_commit_hooks.go)\\n\\nIn the `postCommitActionHandler` struct (line 611), add:\\n```go\\ncondenseAttempted bool  // true if condensation was attempted (regardless of success)\\n```\\n\\n#### 2. Set `condenseAttempted` in handler methods (manual_commit_hooks.go)\\n\\nIn `HandleCondense` (line 650) and `HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched` (line 676), set `h.condenseAttempted = true` before calling `condenseAndUpdateState` when `shouldCondense` is true.\\n\\n#### 3. Record checkpoint ID on attempt, not just success (manual_commit_hooks.go, line 1017)\\n\\nChange:\\n```go\\nif handler.condensed && state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n```\\nTo:\\n```go\\nif handler.condenseAttempted && state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n```\\n\\nThis ensures the checkpoint ID is recorded even when condensation failed (empty transcript).\\n\\n#### 4. Handle `ErrCheckpointNotFound` in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` (manual_commit_hooks.go, ~line 2232)\\n\\nAfter `store.UpdateCommitted` fails with `ErrCheckpointNotFound`, fall back to `CondenseSession`:\\n\\n```go\\nupdateErr := store.UpdateCommitted(ctx, checkpoint.UpdateCommittedOptions{...})\\nif updateErr != nil {\\n    if errors.Is(updateErr, checkpoint.ErrCheckpointNotFound) {\\n        // Checkpoint was never created (e.g., transcript was empty at post-commit time).\\n        // Now that the full transcript is available, create it from scratch.\\n        _, condenseErr := s.CondenseSession(ctx, repo, cpID, state, nil)\\n        if condenseErr != nil {\\n            logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"finalize: deferred condensation failed\\\",\\n                slog.String(\\\"checkpoint_id\\\", cpIDStr),\\n                slog.String(\\\"error\\\", condenseErr.Error()),\\n            )\\n            errCount++\\n        } else {\\n            logging.Info(logCtx, \\\"finalize: deferred checkpoint created\\\",\\n                slog.String(\\\"checkpoint_id\\\", cpIDStr),\\n                slog.String(\\\"session_id\\\", state.SessionID),\\n            )\\n        }\\n        continue\\n    }\\n    // Original error handling for other failures\\n    logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"finalize: failed to update checkpoint\\\", ...)\\n    errCount++\\n    continue\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### 5. Don't change carry-forward or state update logic\\n\\nWhen condensation fails at post-commit:\\n- `state.FilesTouched` is preserved (not cleared) -- correct, needed for deferred condensation\\n- `state.BaseCommit` stays at old commit -- correct, shadow branch is at old commit\\n- Shadow branch is preserved (line 1072) -- correct, `CondenseSession` can find it\\n- `state.CheckpointTranscriptStart` is not updated -- correct, scoping still works\\n\\nAfter deferred `CondenseSession` succeeds at stop time, we don't need to update state because the session is ending (HandleTurnEnd is the last hook before cleanup).\\n\\n#### 6. Unit tests\\n\\nAdd tests to `phase_postcommit_test.go`:\\n\\n**Test 1: `TestPostCommit_ActiveSession_RecordsTurnCheckpointIDs_OnCondensationFailure`**\\n- Set up an ACTIVE session with empty transcript\\n- Run PostCommit -- condensation fails\\n- Verify `TurnCheckpointIDs` still contains the checkpoint ID\\n\\n**Test 2: `TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation`**\\n- Set up state with `TurnCheckpointIDs` containing an ID that has no checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- Write a non-empty transcript to disk\\n- Call `HandleTurnEnd`\\n- Verify the checkpoint was created on `entire/checkpoints/v1` via `CondenseSession`\\n\\n**Test 3: `TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation_StillEmpty`**\\n- Same setup but transcript is still empty at stop time\\n- Verify graceful failure (error logged, no panic)\\n\\n### Edge cases and concerns\\n\\n1. **Multiple commits in one turn**: If there are 2 commits and the first fails condensation but the second succeeds, `TurnCheckpointIDs` has both IDs. At stop time, `UpdateCommitted` succeeds for the second (updates transcript), and the deferred `CondenseSession` creates the first. Both work correctly.\\n\\n2. **`committedFiles` being nil**: When `CondenseSession` is called with `nil` committedFiles, files touched won't be filtered. This means the checkpoint may list files not in that specific commit. This is acceptable -- it's a minor over-attribution vs having no checkpoint at all. The files ARE agent-touched files, just potentially from a broader scope.\\n\\n3. **Attribution accuracy**: At stop time, `CondenseSession` resolves attribution using `state.AttributionBaseCommit` and current HEAD. Since HEAD has moved (post-commit), the attribution will cover the full diff from base to HEAD, not just the specific commit. This is slightly less precise but still correct in direction. For agents like Cursor where this bug manifests, there's typically one commit per turn, so the attribution is exact.\\n\\n4. **Shadow branch state**: The shadow branch from the old base commit is preserved when condensation fails. `CondenseSession` at stop time will find it and prefer the live transcript over the shadow branch copy (line 458-467). This is correct.\\n\\n5. **No behavior change for working agents**: For Claude Code and