})\\nif updateErr != nil {\\n    if errors.Is(updateErr, checkpoint.ErrCheckpointNotFound) {\\n        // Checkpoint wasn't created at post-commit time (e.g., transcript was empty).\\n        // Now that the full transcript is available, create it via CondenseSession.\\n        _, condenseErr := s.CondenseSession(ctx, repo, cpID, state, nil)\\n        if condenseErr != nil {\\n            logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"finalize: deferred condensation failed\\\", ...)\\n            errCount++\\n        } else {\\n            logging.Info(logCtx, \\\"finalize: deferred checkpoint created\\\", ...)\\n        }\\n        continue\\n    }\\n    // Original error path for other failures\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`CondenseSession` with `nil` committedFiles skips file filtering (line 158) and uses files from session data as-is — acceptable since files ARE agent-touched, just not filtered to a specific commit.\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/phase_postcommit_test.go`\\n\\nAdd unit tests:\\n\\n1. **`TestPostCommit_ActiveSession_RecordsTurnCheckpointIDs_OnCondensationFailure`** — ACTIVE session with empty transcript → condensation fails → verify `TurnCheckpointIDs` still contains the checkpoint ID\\n2. **`TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation`** — `TurnCheckpointIDs` contains ID with no checkpoint on metadata branch + non-empty transcript on disk → verify checkpoint created via `CondenseSession`\\n3. **`TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation_TranscriptStillEmpty`** — Same setup but transcript still empty → verify graceful failure (error logged, no panic)\\n\\n## Why This Is Safe\\n\\n- **No behavior change for working agents:** Claude Code, Gemini, etc. flush transcripts before committing. For them, `condenseAttempted = true` AND `condensed = true`, so `TurnCheckpointIDs` is recorded as before. `UpdateCommitted` succeeds at stop time — the `ErrCheckpointNotFound` fallback is never hit.\\n- **Carry-forward unaffected:** The carry-forward logic (line 