ssionId\":\"061fd814-f357-4c55-a9c5-5b97c5911bf5\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"inherited-exploring-treehouse\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01HhDnzSAY11UQAfawp3jXbP\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01RQceSpsNWNcLWYo8BzH6gz\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"allowedPrompts\":[{\"tool\":\"Bash\",\"prompt\":\"run fmt, lint, and tests (unit, canary, e2e cursor-cli)\"}],\"plan\":\"# Fix: Deferred condensation when live transcript is empty at commit time\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCI run [22840528443](https://github.com/entireio/cli/actions/runs/22840528443) shows 42/43 cursor-cli E2E tests passing after our config isolation fix. The single failure is `TestMultiSessionSequential` — a **real-bug** in the CLI where condensation fails silently and is never retried.\\n\\n**Root cause:** When Cursor commits mid-turn, the post-commit hook tries to condense session data to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. For the second session, the live transcript file hasn't been flushed yet by Cursor, so `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript` returns `\\\"live transcript is empty\\\"`. The checkpoint ID (`1f78a5eea34d`) was already written to the commit trailer by `prepare-commit-msg`, but:\\n1. `condenseAndUpdateState` returns `false` → `handler.condensed = false`\\n2. Line 1017: `if handler.condensed && state.Phase.IsActive()` → FALSE → checkpoint ID NOT recorded in `TurnCheckpointIDs`\\n3. At stop time, `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` finds `TurnCheckpointIDs` empty → no-op\\n4. Result: commit trailer points to nonexistent checkpoint metadata\\n\\n## Triage Classification\\n\\n| Test | Agent | Classification | Evidence |\\n|------|-------|----------------|----------|\\n| TestMultiSessionSequential | cursor-cli | **real-bug** | `entire.log` WARN: \\\"condensation failed: live transcript is empty\\\"; checkpoint `1f78a5eea34d` missing from `entire/checkpoints/v1` tree |\\n\\n## Fix: Record checkpoint IDs on attempt + deferred CondenseSession at stop time\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n#### Change 1: Add `condenseAttempted` flag to `postCommitActionHandler` (line 611)\\n\\nAdd a new field alongside `condensed`:\\n```go\\ntype postCommitActionHandler struct {\\n    // ... existing fields ...\\n    condensed          bool // true if condensation succeeded\\n    condenseAttempted  bool // true if condensation was attempted (even if it failed)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### Change 2: Set `condenseAttempted` in handler methods (lines 650, 676)\\n\\nIn both `HandleCondense` and `HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched`, set `h.condenseAttempted = true` when `shouldCondense` is true (before calling `condenseAndUpdateState`):\\n\\n```go\\nif shouldCondense {\\n    h.condenseAttempted = true\\n    h.condensed = h.s.condenseAndUpdateState(...)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### Change 3: Record checkpoint ID on attempt, not just success (line 1017)\\n\\nChange the guard from requiring success to requiring attempt:\\n```go\\n// Before:\\nif handler.condensed && state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n    state.TurnCheckpointIDs = append(...)\\n}\\n\\n// After:\\nif handler.condenseAttempted && state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n    state.TurnCheckpointIDs = append(...)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis ensures the checkpoint ID is recorded even when condensation failed due to an empty transcript. The existing carry-forward logic (line 1027) still gates on `handler.condensed`, so carry-forward and shadow branch cleanup remain correct.\\n\\n#### Change 4: Handle `ErrCheckpointNotFound` in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` (~line 2232)\\n\\nWhen `UpdateCommitted` returns `ErrCheckpointNotFound`, fall back to `CondenseSession`:\\n\\n```go\\nupdateErr := store.UpdateCommitted(ctx, checkpoint.UpdateCommittedOptions{...})\\nif updateErr != nil {\\n    if errors.Is(updateErr, checkpoint.ErrCheckpointNotFound) {\\n        // Checkpoint wasn't created at post-commit time (e.g., transcript was empty).\\n        // Now that the full transcript is available, create it via CondenseSession.\\n        _, condenseErr := s.CondenseSession(ctx, repo, cpID, state, nil)\\n        if condenseErr != nil {\\n            logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"finalize: deferred condensation failed\\\", ...)\\n            errCount++\\n        } else {\\n            logging.Info(logCtx, \\\"finalize: deferred checkpoint created\\\", ...)\\n        }\\n        continue\\n    }\\n    // Original error path for other failures\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`CondenseSession` with `nil` committedFiles skips file filtering (line 158) and uses files from session data as-is — acceptable since files ARE agent-touched, just not filtered to a specific commit.\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/phase_postcommit_test.go`\\n\\nAdd unit tests:\\n\\n1. **`TestPostCommit_ActiveSession_RecordsTurnCheckpointIDs_OnCondensationFailure`** — ACTIVE session with empty transcript → condensation fails → verify `TurnCheckpointIDs` still contains the checkpoint ID\\n2. **`TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation`** — `TurnCheckpointIDs` contains ID with no checkpoint on metadata branch + non-empty transcript on disk → verify checkpoint created via `CondenseSession`\\n3. **`TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation_TranscriptStillEmpty`** — Same setup but transcript still empty → verify graceful failure (error logged, no panic)\\n\\n## Why This Is Safe\\n\\n- **No behavior change for working agents:** Claude Code, Gemini, etc. flush transcripts before committing. For them, `condenseAttempted = true` AND `condensed = true`, so `TurnCheckpointIDs` is recorded as before. `UpdateCommitted` succeeds at stop time — the `ErrCheckpointNotFound` fallback is never hit.\\n- **Carry-forward unaffected:** The carry-forward logic (line 1027) still gates on `handler.condensed`, not `handler.condenseAttempted`. Shadow branch preservation (line 1072) also gates on `condensed`. Both remain correct.\\n- **State remains consistent:** When condensation fails, `state.BaseCommit` stays at the old commit and the shadow branch is preserved — exactly what `CondenseSession` needs at stop time to find the shadow data.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint           # Static checks\\nmise run test                           # Unit tests (includes new tests)\\nmise run test:e2e:canary                # Canary (Vogon) — no API cost\\nmise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli    # Full cursor-cli suite — verify fix\\n```\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":833,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":120101,\"output_tokens\":92,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":833,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYs2hnNm7mEYvs4qC3j2F\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"fa89b98c-1e69-46de-97d8-b0bed793dbfa\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T06:26:17.074Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"fa89b98c-1e69-46de-97d8-b0bed793dbfa\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"061fd814-f357-4c55-a9c5-5b97c5911bf5\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"inherited-exploring-treehouse\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"The user doesn't want to proceed with this tool use. The tool use was rejected (eg. if it was a file edit, the new_string was NOT written to the file). STOP what you are doing and wait for the user to tell you how to proceed.\",\"is_error\":true,\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01RQceSpsNWNcLWYo8BzH6gz\"}]},\"uuid\":\"19b62870-4d09-4575-b78a-e5a36a685f73\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T06:27:13.113Z\",\"toolUseR